'''Vly Mountain''' is a [[mountain]] located [[Greene County, New York|Greene County]], [[New York]]. 
The mountain is part of the [[Catskill Mountains]].
Vly Mountain is flanked to the northwest by [[Bearpen Mountain (Greene County, New York)|Bearpen Mountain]].

The north side of Vly Mountain drains into Little West Kill, thence into [[Schoharie Creek]], the [[Mohawk River]], the [[Hudson River]], and into [[New York Bay]].
The east side of Vly Mtn. drains into West Kill, thence into Schoharie Creek.
The south and west sides of Vly drain into Vly Creek, thence into Bush Kill, Dry Brook, the [[East Branch Delaware River|East Branch]] of the [[Delaware River]], and into [[Delaware Bay]].

